<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Prelude to a Dwarven Battle</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Drugar">Drugar</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 3:00 p.m. 6/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Prelude to a Dwarven Battle<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>"Shut yer trap, laddie, and perhaps I'll get to tellin' ye my story. But first, I'm goin' ta finish me drink! Nothin' compares to a good draught of dwarf spirits.. that'll pu hair on yer face, aye laddie. Beats out the tasteless wine those pasty, lanky point-ears brew up in their bloody trees and marble tow'rs, it does."

<P>Drugar takes a long draw from the mug in front of him.
<P>"Aright, aright I'll tell ye."
<P>"Me father was a blacksmith and weapons dealer of highest renown. His specialty was armor, and he was known far and wide, much as I am today.. 'Hail, mighty Drugar' ye all say ta me when I get off the boot, ya do."
<P>"When I was young, a six-fingered man wearing a cloak that his face might be concealed came to my father and requested that a special ringmail tunic be made. My father agreed, and for the next three months he poured his soul into that armor."
<P>"When the man returned, he told my father he would only pay half of the agreed price. My father refused, and without a word the six-fingered man ran a sword through my father's heart, he did. He took the armor, and fled."
<P>"Since that day, I have devoted myself to my father's trade, and to the use of the weapons I forge. Brell Serilis saw fit to bestow upon me his powers.. and one day, I will find the six-fingered man. And when I do, I will say to him, 'Hello. My name is Drugar. You killed my father. Prepare to die.'"
<P>To be continued...
<P><any resemblance of the above story to a certain character in a certain movie is probably in no way coincidental>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
